      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The board OF works today de-\ncided to recommend to the council\nthat the building OF the East\nSprague av. fill be undertaken at\nonce. The work will be done by\ncontract, g. B. Dennis being the\nsuccessful bidder. His bid was\n$4,000,\n\n\nThe matter was held up pending\naction by the w. w, p. and the In\nland Empire railway systems.\nBoth the w. w. p. and the Graves\npeople before offered to pay 5000\neach toward the cost.\n\n\nThey have now agreed to pay\nse6,350, the Inland Empire system\n$4,000 for its subway and the w.\nw. p. for the work on the fill\nwhich its lines will require."
    }
